ACT:
 Banking law and practice - Liberation of Goa and other areas from Portuguese rule and integration with India - Head office of the bank removed all documents to Lisbon on the eve of liberation - President promulgated regulations constituting an independent bank - Custodian empowered to realise all debts - Agreements entered into and loans granted by head office in Lisbon - Custodian - If could recover debts - Position in banking law and practice discussed - Promissory notes and bills of exchange if necessary to be produced at the time of recovery of debts.
 
